transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Mr. David Lofay, did I say that right?

Speaker 2: This message has been transcribed.

Speaker 1: Hello?

Speaker 2: David?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: Did I say that right?

Speaker 1: Lofay?

Speaker 2: It's Lofay.

Speaker 1: Lofay.

Speaker 2: Mr. David, just out of the goodness of my heart and as an American and a veteran,

Speaker 1: I walked down there with my .338 Brawling and my AR-15,

Speaker 2: and stomped on the door and I said,

Speaker 1: get his damn thing ready.

Speaker 2: I want his money now.

Speaker 1: I'm not leaving.

Speaker 2: I'm going to unload this clip,

Speaker 1: and this thing will not stop unless the clip is all emptied out,

Speaker 2: and then they did it.

Speaker 1: So go check it out.

Speaker 2: Check your account now.

Speaker 1: Oh, okay.

Speaker 2: No, it's not on here right now.

Speaker 1: It would get on there that fast anyway,

Speaker 2: but it gets on there that fast when you're taking the payment.

Speaker 1: No, but it will.

Speaker 2: If you did a credit card or PayPal, it goes immediately.

Speaker 1: If you did like a debit card, try refreshing your screen.

Speaker 2: Especially with Discover, Amex goes pretty quick.

Speaker 1: Yeah, this is an Amex card.

Speaker 2: Yeah, it should be pretty quick.

Speaker 1: Oh, no, no.

Speaker 2: The only one I'm seeing is the one from January 11th.

Speaker 1: Yeah, just give it time.

Speaker 2: It's from January 21st, and that's just a $10 charge.

Speaker 1: And just give it time, and let me give you my extension

Speaker 2: so you don't get passed around,

Speaker 1: because I would have thought like you work the streets of Vegas, brother,

Speaker 2: the way how many people you touched on just to get this done.

Speaker 1: But, Mike, I didn't mean it that way.

Speaker 2: But I'm just saying you got passed around.

Speaker 1: It's not a good thing.

Speaker 2: My name is KT Goodrich, Mr. Lofe, and my extension is 0037.

Speaker 1: But I assure you, I went down there, I kicked down doors,

Speaker 2: and I was going to choke some people.

Speaker 1: And they said, oh, it shows on your screen, KT,

Speaker 2: but it actually hasn't been processed.

Speaker 1: Let's do it now.

Speaker 2: So December has been done on my end because the way I roll, I'm American.

Speaker 1: I roll American style to the day I die, you know, to the wheels roll off.

Speaker 2: Perfect. I love it.

Speaker 1: Yeah, if there's any consolation to you.

Speaker 2: But, you know, if you can, go to support at scoreblue.com.

Speaker 1: I'm up for review, and as a veteran,

Speaker 2: any dollar would count here in California unless we get a new governor.

Speaker 1: As you know, we need one.

Speaker 2: We need one.

Speaker 1: I was going to move to Georgia because your guys are getting money back

Speaker 2: for whatever money they don't use from a Kemp.

Speaker 1: That's right.

Speaker 2: Is it Kemp?

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: What's his name?

Speaker 1: He's right out.

Speaker 2: This is the end of his second term, so he's good for him.

Speaker 1: Damn.

Speaker 2: I'm sure he – I hope he trained someone or he had some backup

Speaker 1: because if not –

Speaker 2: He's really good.

Speaker 1: I don't say that too much about too many politicians.

Speaker 2: And my daughter's a schoolteacher.

Speaker 1: He just gave them $2,000.

Speaker 2: Oh, good, man.

Speaker 1: You know, it's so good to see something like that and just, like, it's –

Speaker 2: you know, I don't know how to say this,

Speaker 1: but these guys know that they're not doing their jobs

Speaker 2: and then they still just – how do they live?

Speaker 1: How do they live with themselves knowing that they knew when they went

Speaker 2: into office and then when you have someone nice and beautiful that comes

Speaker 1: around like a breath of fresh air, it's kind of like they just give us

Speaker 2: a little cracker and then they go on and we deal with the bad again.

Speaker 1: Then they give us a little cracker.

Speaker 2: I don't know.

Speaker 1: God controls all, but if you can go to support at scoreblue.com

Speaker 2: and let them know how you felt about me organically

Speaker 1: and how I satisfied your call.

Speaker 2: If things change on your end and you want to start this up again,

Speaker 1: let me know, 0037-KT-DIDRICH,

Speaker 2: and I'll make sure you get what you deserve, sir.

Speaker 1: Okay, I appreciate all your help, man.

Speaker 2: I'll do that now.

Speaker 1: Yeah, thank you so much, sir, and I appreciate you.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Be well and stay warm over there.

Speaker 2: I know it's cold as hell.

Speaker 1: Yeah, it is.

Speaker 2: You may even get snow.

Speaker 1: Well, I pray for you guys' safety and security over anything, you know,

Speaker 2: safety and security.

Speaker 1: All right, man.

Speaker 2: All right, bud.

Speaker 1: You take care.

Speaker 2: Thank you, man.

Speaker 1: You bet.

Speaker 2: That's how we roll.

Speaker 1: Adios.
